{"analytics_identifier":"OT1324","base_path":"/government/organisations/the-equality-hub","content_id":"0f8a33d1-f7fa-4f7a-a1d0-8e3424ab01b2","description":"We focus on disability policy, ethnic disparities, gender equality, LGBT rights and the overall framework of equality legislation for the UK.","details":{"acronym":"","alternative_format_contact_email":"accessible.formats@cabinetoffice.gov.uk","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We focus on disability policy, ethnic disparities, gender equality, LGBT rights and the overall framework of equality legislation for the UK.</p>\n</div>","brand":"cabinet-office","default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5fdb2d75d3bf7f40d96f7c7a/s960_EH_gov.uk.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5fdb2d758fa8f54d6480f5b6/s300_EH_gov.uk.png"},"foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"single-identity","formatted_title":"Equality Hub"},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[],"ordered_featured_documents":[{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/disability-minister-pays-tribute-to-paralympicsgb-athletes-for-inspiring-the-next-generation-in-paris","image":{"alt_text":"The Minister for Social Security and Disability, Sir Stephen Timms MP, speaking with gold medal Para taekwondo athlete, Matt Bush.","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/66df163f0f4ba0621b0866a6/s712_Paralympics_2024_PN_-_960_x_640.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/66df163fd65d5c23df08669e/s465_Paralympics_2024_PN_-_960_x_640.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/66df163f45cb18e102ebabcd/Paralympics_2024_PN_-_960_x_640.png"},"public_updated_at":"2024-09-09T16:32:59.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Minister for Social Security and Disability, Sir Stephen Timms highlighted the importance of disability inclusion and accessibility as he met with ParalympicsGB athletes at the 17th Summer Paralympic Games in Paris.</p>\n</div>","title":"Disability Minister pays tribute to ParalympicsGB athletes for ‘inspiring the next generation in Paris’"},{"document_type":"Press release","href":"/government/news/new-disability-action-plan-to-make-uk-most-accessible-place-in-the-world","image":{"alt_text":"graphic with the words \"Disability Action Plan: 32 practical measures to improve disabled people's daily lives\"","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/65c114fe63a23d0013c82264/s712_DAP_PN_1.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/65c114fe704282000d752275/s465_DAP_PN_1.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/65c114fe7042820013752254/DAP_PN_1.png"},"public_updated_at":"2024-02-05T16:40:24.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Government has launched its new Disability Action Plan – 32 steps it is taking to make the UK the most accessible place in the world for disabled people to live, work and thrive.</p>\n</div>","title":"New Disability Action Plan to make UK most accessible place in the world"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/new-deputies-appointed-as-alun-francis-confirmed-as-smc-chair","image":{"alt_text":"Alun Francis OBE, Chair of the Social Mobility Commission","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/655f295f3523490012b3f90e/s712_s465_afrancis2_crop.jpeg","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/655f295f352349000db3f918/s465_s465_afrancis2_crop.jpeg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/655f295f4d0864000dd039ae/s465_afrancis2_crop.jpeg"},"public_updated_at":"2023-11-10T11:59:14.000+00:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Alun Francis has been appointed permanent Chair of the Social Mobility Commission (SMC), with Resham Kotecha and Rob Wilson serving as deputies.</p>\n</div>","title":"New deputies appointed as Alun Francis confirmed as SMC Chair"},{"document_type":"News story","href":"/government/news/bsl-users-appointed-to-board-advising-government-on-key-issues-for-deaf-people","image":{"alt_text":"","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/645e066f2c06a3000cc05bf5/s712_bsl.png","medium_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/645e066fad8a03001138b364/s465_bsl.png","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/645e066fad8a03001138b363/bsl.png"},"public_updated_at":"2023-04-24T17:14:46.000+01:00","summary":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Speaking at the British Deaf Association’s BSL Conference, the Minister for Disabled People, Health and Work, Tom Pursglove MP, has appointed 16 members to the new British Sign Language (BSL) Advisory Board, which will advise the government on key issues impacting the Deaf community.</p>\n</div>","title":"BSL users appointed to board advising government on key issues for Deaf people"}],"ordered_featured_links":[{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/disability-unit","title":"Disability Unit"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/government-equalities-office","title":"Government Equalities Office"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/race-disparity-unit","title":"Race Disparity Unit"},{"href":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/social-mobility-commission","title":"Social Mobility Commission"}],"ordered_promotional_features":[],"organisation_featuring_priority":"news","organisation_govuk_status":{"status":"changed_name","updated_at":"2024-10-09T00:00:00.000+01:00","url":""},"organisation_political":false,"organisation_type":"other","secondary_corporate_information_pages":"","social_media_links":[{"href":"https://twitter.com/DisabilityGovUK","service_type":"twitter","title":"Disability Unit Twitter"},{"href":"https://twitter.com/ehgovuk","service_type":"twitter","title":"Equality Hub Twitter"},{"href":"https://twitter.com/SMCommission","service_type":"twitter","title":"SMC 